fields.description: A brush, that fills a surface with a solid color.

fields.name: linear_gradient
fields.description:
A brush, that fills a surface with a linear gradient, which is defined by two points in local coordinates
and a set of stop points. See [`GradientPoint`] for more info.

fields.name: radial_gradient
fields.description:
A brush, that fills a surface with a radial gradient, which is defined by a center point in local coordinates
and a set of stop points. See [`GradientPoint`] for more info.

variants.description: No grabbing of the cursor is performed.

The cursor is confined to the window area.

There's no guarantee that the cursor will be hidden. You should hide it by yourself if you
want to do so.

## Platform-specific

- **macOS:** Not implemented. Always returns [`ExternalError::NotSupported`] for now.
- **iOS / Android / Web:** Always returns an [`ExternalError::NotSupported`].

There's no guarantee that the cursor will be hidden. You should hide it by yourself if you
want to do so.

fields.name: feature
fields.description:
Additional data that contains a kind of the feature with which
intersection was detected as well as its index.

# Important notes.

FeatureId::Face might have index that is greater than amount of triangles in
a triangle mesh, this means that intersection was detected from "back" side of
a face. To "fix" that index, simply subtract amount of triangles of a triangle
mesh from the value.
